archetypes.name: Consistent Contenders
archetypes.representative_drivers: Terry Labonte, Jim Paschal, Buddy Baker
archetypes.description: Reliable drivers who regularly finish in the top-10 with occasional wins. Solid performers you can count on.

archetypes.name: Race Winners
archetypes.representative_drivers: Jeff Gordon, Jimmie Johnson, Kyle Busch
archetypes.description: Drivers who regularly win races and compete for championships. Solid performers with proven winning ability.

archetypes.name: Mid-Pack Drivers
archetypes.representative_drivers: Ed Negre, Bill Champion, Banjo Matthews
archetypes.description: Drivers who typically finish in the middle of the field. Solid contributors to the sport.

archetypes.name: Veteran Journeymen
archetypes.representative_drivers: Sterling Marlin, Dave Marcis, Kyle Petty
archetypes.description: Long-career drivers with moderate success. The experienced backbone of NASCAR competition.

archetypes.name: Elite Champions
archetypes.representative_drivers: Richard Petty, David Pearson, Darrell Waltrip
archetypes.description: The absolute best drivers in NASCAR history. Multiple wins per season and consistent championship contenders.

archetypes.name: Backfield Runners
archetypes.representative_drivers: Billy Carden, Barney Smith, Slim Brown
archetypes.description: Drivers who consistently ran in the back of the field throughout their careers.
